<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Mutation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mutation/</link><description>Recent content in Mutation on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mutation/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] GraphQL: Error Response from Server Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/graphql-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/graphql-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="graphql-error-response-from-server"&gt;GraphQL: Error Response from Server&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a GraphQL server returns an error in its &lt;code&gt;errors&lt;/code&gt; array. Unlike REST, GraphQL often returns a 200 status with errors in the response body, making them easy to miss.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common error messages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;message&amp;quot;: &amp;quot;Cannot query field 'email' on type 'User'.&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;message&amp;quot;: &amp;quot;Field 'createUser' is missing required arguments: name, email&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;message&amp;quot;: &amp;quot;Not authorized to perform this action&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;message&amp;quot;: &amp;quot;Internal server error&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;{ errors: [...], data: null }&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;{ errors: [...], data: { partial: &amp;quot;data&amp;quot; } }&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GraphQL servers always return a JSON object with an &lt;code&gt;errors&lt;/code&gt; array (when errors occur) and optionally a &lt;code&gt;data&lt;/code&gt; field. HTTP status is usually 200.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Kotlin GraphQL Error — GraphQL Query Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/graphql-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/kotlin/graphql-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="graphql-error--graphql-query-fix"&gt;GraphQL Error — GraphQL Query Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A GraphQL error occurs when a GraphQL query or mutation fails. Unlike REST APIs that use HTTP status codes, GraphQL always returns 200 OK but includes errors in the response body.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GraphQL responses have a standard format with &lt;code&gt;data&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;errors&lt;/code&gt; fields. Errors can be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Validation errors&lt;/strong&gt; — query doesn&amp;rsquo;t match the schema.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execution errors&lt;/strong&gt; — error during resolver execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Authentication errors&lt;/strong&gt; — missing or invalid credentials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partial data&lt;/strong&gt; — some fields resolved, others failed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] SwiftUI @State Mutation Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/swiftui-state-error-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/swift/swiftui-state-error-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="swiftui-state-mutation-error-fix"&gt;SwiftUI: @State Mutation Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A SwiftUI @State mutation error occurs when you try to modify a @State property from outside its owning view or in an invalid context.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;@State&lt;/code&gt; properties are managed by SwiftUI and can only be mutated within the view that owns them. Modifying @State from a different view or from a non-main-actor context causes runtime errors or warnings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modifying @State from a child view&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Setting @State in async context without MainActor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using @State on reference types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trying to mutate @State in view initializer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-use-binding-for-child-views"&gt;1. Use @Binding for child views&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Child tries to modify parent&amp;#39;s @State&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ChildView&lt;/span&gt;: View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; @State &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; count = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Separate state&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; body: some View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Button(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Tap&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { count &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use @Binding&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ChildView&lt;/span&gt;: View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; @Binding &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; count: Int
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; body: some View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Button(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Tap&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;) { count &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ParentView&lt;/span&gt;: View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; @State &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; count = &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; body: some View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ChildView(count: &lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;count)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-use-mainactor-for-async-updates"&gt;2. Use MainActor for async updates&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Modifying @State from background&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;loadData&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Task {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data = await fetchFromAPI()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; count = data.count &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Warning: mutation from non-isolated context&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Dispatch to MainActor&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;func&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;loadData&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Task {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data = await fetchFromAPI()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; await MainActor.run {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; count = data.count
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-use-observedobject-for-reference-types"&gt;3. Use @ObservedObject for reference types&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: @State with class&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;@State &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; user = User() &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong: State for reference types&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use @StateObject or @ObservedObject&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;@StateObject &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; user = User()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;@ObservedObject &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; user: User
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-dont-mutate-in-view-body"&gt;4. Don&amp;rsquo;t mutate in view body&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-swift" data-lang="swift"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Mutating in body&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; body: some View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; count &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Error: mutation in computed property&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Text(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;count&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use task modifier&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; body: some View {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Text(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;\(&lt;/span&gt;count&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .task {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; count = await fetchCount()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="swiftui-error"&gt;SwiftUI Error&lt;/a&gt; — general SwiftUI errors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="swift-concurrency-error-v2"&gt;Swift Concurrency Error&lt;/a&gt; — concurrency issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="swiftui-list-error"&gt;SwiftUI List Error&lt;/a&gt; — list rendering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>